title: AC’s Fusselman gets SCAC weekly honor
text:
AC’s Fusselman gets SCAC weekly honor Herald Democrat 
Austin College volleyball player Rachel Fusselman has been named the Southern Collegiate Athletic Conference Defensive Player of the Week, the league office has announced. 
Fusselman, a senior libero from Trophy Club, averaged 7.2 digs-per-set in three matches last week. Fusselman totaled 72 digs for the week to help the ‘Roos go 2-1 against a trio of SCAC opponents, and twice tallied more than 20 digs. She notched a weekend high of 30 digs in a 3-1 victory over Dallas. This is the third time in the first six weeks of the season that Fusselman has earned this award. 
She also recently became Austin College’s career leader in digs, and the first player in program history to surpass 2,000 digs for her career.
